{
  "info": {
    "name": "Tupay Ledger & Settlement Engine",
    "description": "Complete API flow for the Tupay cross-border remittance backend. Run requests in order: Login -> 2FA Verify -> Swap -> Ledger -> Webhook.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "tupay-engine"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000/api",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "auth_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "wallet_id",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "webhook_secret",
      "value": "mock-secret-for-testing",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Login",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "if (json.token) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', json.token);",
              "    console.log('Token saved:', json.token);",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"test@tupay.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/login",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["login"]
        },
        "description": "Authenticate with email and password. Token is automatically saved to the collection variable `auth_token`. Note: this does NOT grant access to 2FA-protected endpoints yet."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Verify 2FA",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "console.log('2FA response:', json.message);"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n    \"code\": \"123456\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/2fa/verify",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["2fa", "verify"]
        },
        "description": "Submit a 6-digit TOTP code from your authenticator app (Google Authenticator, Authy). The 2FA secret was printed to the console when you ran `php artisan db:seed`. On success, a Redis key is set for 15 minutes that unlocks swap endpoints."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Execute Swap (NGN -> CNY)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n    \"amount\": 100000\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/swap",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["swap"]
        },
        "description": "Exchange NGN for CNY. `amount` is in kobo (subunits). 100,000 kobo = 1,000 NGN. Requires a valid 2FA session (step 2 must have been completed within the last 15 minutes). Returns both the debit (NGN) and credit (CNY) transaction records."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Get Ledger (NGN Wallet)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/ledger/{{wallet_id}}?page=1",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["ledger", "{{wallet_id}}"],
          "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "1" }]
        },
        "description": "Retrieve paginated transaction history for a wallet. Default `wallet_id` is 1 (NGN wallet for the seeded user). Returns 15 records per page, ordered by most recent first. Change the wallet_id collection variable to 2 for the CNY wallet."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Settlement Webhook",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Compute HMAC-SHA256 signature using CryptoJS",
              "const secret = pm.collectionVariables.get('webhook_secret');",
              "const body = pm.request.body.raw;",
              "const signature = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(body, secret).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);",
              "pm.request.headers.add({ key: 'X-Tupay-Signature', value: signature });",
              "console.log('Computed signature:', signature);"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n    \"provider_reference\": \"PARTNER-REF-001\",\n    \"status\": \"completed\",\n    \"amount\": 52000,\n    \"wallet_id\": 2\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/webhooks/settlement",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["webhooks", "settlement"]
        },
        "description": "Simulate a third-party settlement partner confirming an RMB payout. The pre-request script automatically computes and attaches the HMAC-SHA256 signature using CryptoJS. Send this request twice with the same `provider_reference` to verify idempotency — the second call returns 200 (already processed) without crediting the wallet again. Requires the queue worker to be running for actual ledger update."
      },
      "response": []
    }
  ]
}
